name: Rock Jaw - Gebieter über die östliche Grenze

description: Energized from their dreams and ready to re-enter the fray, the kids take on a risky mission to save their parents from the Alabaster Shadows Community Council and set loose an imprisoned monster. But can they fight off attackers while conducting an intricate ceremony—backwards? Even if they succeed, is this really over? And whatever happened to Mr. Randolph?
name: Chapter Six

description: This is your chance to peek into All-New, All-Different Marvel continuing this November! See the explosively striking images of Marvel's new lineup coming in the latter half of 2015 into 2016! Brought to you by the industry's top creators! Exciting teams, dynamic characters, deadly villains, dazzling creators and more will be revealed here!

The werewolf camp has a brand new dangerous addition as Locked Down's sister Dakota rides into town, bringing with her even more chaos than the town may be able to handle! Meanwhile Teddy has to try to come to terms with the loss of his father, reconcile with his ex Gwen and attempt to solve the mystery of the extremely violent wolf attacks.

Get ready for one wild and hairy thrill ride when the moon and the gas tanks are full and the townies and werewolves go to war!

Vikings killed her and her entire family. Now a year later, on Samhain, Morrigan the Celtic goddess forces Colleen to rise and claim vengeance as Belladonna! In this issue, Belladonna tightens the noose around the neck of her Viking opponents and throws down the gauntlet of final battle! It is time for a reckoning, their entire army against just her! The lands will flood with the blood of the evil as Belladonna is unleashed! Originally presented in Belladonna #4.

The vikings have amassed a huge army and now plain to finish off Belladonna where it all started, her family castle. But she has been preparing for this moment, and now is ready to lay waste to their hordes once and for all! The startling conclusion to the first Belladonna arc is here! Originally presented in Belladonna #5.

Brian Pulido's warrior women of medieval times meet for the first time in this action-packed crossover! Medieval Lady Death and Wolf, on the run from the evil Bishop Vitirio, try to hide out in Wexford Ireland, but have the misfortune of arriving at the same time as Rurik discovers and ancient talisman he can use to control gargoyles, unleashing a wave of evil that washes over the land. Enter Colleen McGrath, better known as Belladonna, brought back to the living once again to protect her people. But she presumes the threat is from the pale-skinned invader and Lady Death has the fight of her life on her hands! Originally presented in Medieval Lady Death / Belladonn #1/2 - #1.

A suburban housewife with a criminal past and a thirst for adrenaline is about to get a top-secret side job: carrying out the government's most dangerous missions.

Renear is tired of playing by the rules. A valedictorian and top athlete in her younger years, she's sacrificed a promising career to tie the knot and play house... isn't there more to life than this? Of course there is - if you're willing to take the shot. It's time the world found out what she is truly capable of. Legendary Comics presents Black Bag, a new espionage thriller written by Chris Roberson (Superman Grounded, Fables, iZombie), featuring artwork by JB Bastos (Night Trap).

Growing up in the Empire of Blood, Tom Lawrence has the life most of his friends dream of -- his father's approval, a warranted place in the workings of the Empire, and a beautiful fiancée. But his past returns to haunt him, and the future becomes bleak as he gets involved with the rebellion and finds the sinister secret behind Aqua Vitae, the lifeblood of the empire. The second issue in a 4-part series.

Journey back to Victorian London for the senses-shattering final chapters in Bloody Mary’s horrific origin story as she shows her husband and her so-called friends what’s waiting on the other side of the mirror! Then, follow her to the rainy back alleys of modern-day Fabletown, where she’s come to collect her bounty...and she’s got a silver bullet for any wolf who stands in her way!

One of the most epic battles of the American West becomes Future Proof, as this one-way time-traveling adventure crashes Sitting Bull's War Party. Agents James and Simon ensure that the Battle of Little Big Horn really is General Custer's last stand. Meanwhile, in 1969 Los Angeles, while the Umbrella Man makes his slow march into the future, he meets a new recruit that will reverberate throughout history.

Note: The digital edition (11/11/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.

The epic OZ trilogy CONCLUDES!

description:
Blessed with the curse of infinite intelligence, there's only one thing Jonas Quantum can't do: play well with others. This thrilling action-adventure series spans cosmic voyages, history-changing inventions, and delusions of grandeur.

In the third issue, Dr. Sorrow unleashes an onslaught of chaos and destruction the world over, forcing Jonas to rise to the challenge. But when 'the smartest man on Earth' gets outsmarted, Quantum realizes that he and his new nemesis have more in common than he ever imagined! It's a high-stakes battle of wits and will as these two masterminds go head to head

volume.name: The Infinite Adventures of Jonas Quantum

description: Catastrophe looms as Veronica and her new friend are hunted through the streets by a "fixer" from Infinite Industries who has been charged with subduing the escaped Subject 74 by any means necessary. Will V and Mr. Collins hold out against this terrible new foe or will Subject 74 be left in the cold?

After years spent training with the strange mystics called Sadhus, James Jensen returns to civilization and unleashes his newfound abilities against the man who destroyed his family. But Jensen soon discovers that Townsend's obsession with the darker occult forces of India have given him supernatural powers of his own. Written by legendary comic scribe, Chuck Dixon.

volume.name: The Sadhu: Birth of the Warrior

description: Akuma makes his move, while Juri and Seth try to double cross the Secret Society. All this plus, is M.Bison... alive!? It's a power-packed issue busting with bad guys!
Spider-Man, Power Man, White Tiger, Iron Fist, and Nova have met their evil matches at Brighton Beach High. Will Power Man's sneezing lead them right to Musty, or right to trouble?

Cut off from Belle Reve and presumed dead in a faraway land, the Suicide Squad are presented with the opportunity to fulfill their greatest wish: killing their jailer, Amanda Waller.
